What are common symptoms of PAD? Leg pain while walking that eases with rest. Numbness, weakness, or cramping in legs or hips. Coldness in one leg or foot. Unhealed sores on toes, feet or legs.
What are common causes and risks for PAD? Smoking, diabetes, high blood-presure, obesity, age, family trends.
How does PAD typically get treated? Exercising and eating heart-healthy foods.
